  "text": "On day 0 after baseline measurements were made, an intravenous infusion of adult sheep plasma (to increase fetal pressures and the mechanical load on the heart valves) or lactated Ringer solution (as an equal volume control) was started using a Minipuls 3 roller pump (Gilson, Middleton, WI). Initial plasma infusion rate was calculated to deliver 18.75 g protein/day (324 Ϯ 23 ml/day) initially, and increased by 3.5% per day to correspond to expected fetal growth, as previously described [CITATION_1] . After 8 days, the plasma infusion group had received a total 2,509 Ϯ 147 ml fluid. In the two-day infusion group, the plasma infusion group had received a total of 800 Ϯ 25 ml fluid. Each control received an identical volume of lactated Ringer solution. Fetuses were randomly assigned to the experimental or control group without regard to sex.",
